// Project vocabulary.
//
// `define` binds a name to a definition string. The defined name then becomes
// usable as a custom block keyword, and tools append its definition to the
// glossary they hand the LLM — so the agent knows what you mean by "aggregate"
// without you re-explaining it in every file.
//
// The conventional home for project-wide vocabulary is a file like this one,
// imported at the top of the entry file.

// Quotes around the definition are recommended for readability, but optional.
define aggregate "A DDD aggregate root. Owns its invariants and never exposes raw internal state."
define policy "A business rule that can be swapped or overridden per deployment."
define adapter "A boundary object translating between our domain and an external system."

// Without quotes — equally valid, just harder to read once it gets long.
define shelf A physical or virtual location where a copy can rest

/*
  Block comments work too, and like line comments they are stripped during
  processing — they never reach the LLM. To say something *to* the agent, use a
  prose block or a ??? marker instead.
*/
